        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 1 at 4:08PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 408 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Diamond Bay, or 9 miles east of Mountain Home, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Byron...                          Vidette...
Diamond Bay...                    Flint Springs...
Gamaliel Landing...               Elizabeth...
Norfork Lake...                   Mitchell...
Bexar...                          Robinson Point Landing...
Viola...                          Wild Cherry...
Henderson...                      Gepp...
Briarcliff...                     Oxford...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
